message: Actually add TS libdef to package. 1.0.5

v2 beta to support react-navigation 2.3.1 (#37)

* v2 beta to support react-navigation 2.3.1

react-navigation had a breaking change for redux users in v2.3.

Fortunately, this change makes the redux implementation more simple and robust.

Unfortunately, it will require a change for redux users. There are additional required arguments for createNavigationPropConstructor

* Avoid screenProps for redux apps

* README changes and style changes
Introducing reduxifyNavigator, the main new thing in 2.0

Add reduxify to types (#40)

* Add reduxify to types

* Add missing peerDependencies: redux

* Remove outdated methods from type definition

* Remove outdated methods from type definition

2.0.3. Make delay of subscriber triggers more narrowly scoped

This functionality is necessary to make sure `react-navigation` behaves correctly, but it also causes confusion when delays are applied to unrelated actions.

Fixes ability to use with react-navigation 3.0 for web (#74)

* Changes imports to use @react-navigation/core

* Also changes peer dependency to @react-navigation/core

Set context in createReduxContainer

Sets `NavigationContext`, `ThemeContext`, and `SafeAreaContext` for downstream consumers

Import from react-navigation instead of @react-navigation/core

Our users are more likely to already have the `react-navigation` libdef installed

Specify react-native-safe-area-context dependency explicitly

It's not guaranteed as a peer dependency until `@react-navigation/core@4`, which is still in alpha

Back out react-native-safe-area-context

This requires linking on native
Import from @react-navigation/core instead of react-navigation to maintain web compatibility
